The '''Premios Sur Award for Best Actress''' ({{lang-es|Premio Sur de a Mejor actriz protagónica}}), is an award given annually by the [[Argentine Academy of Cinematography Arts and Sciences]] to the best actress in Argentina for that year. The award was suspended in 1955 with the military coup d'état known as the [[Revolución Libertadora]] and not revived until 2006, after the present Academy was founded in 2004.<ref name="Premios Sur History">{{cite web|title=Su Historia| url=http://academiadecine.org.ar/la-academia/su-historia/|website=Academia de las Artes y Ciencias Cinematográficas de la Argentina|publisher=Academia de las Artes y Ciencias Cinematográficas de la Argentina|accessdate=28 June 2015|location=Buenos Aires, Argentina|language=Spanish}}</ref>
