{{Infobox video game | title = Soviet Challenge: Javelin 1980 | developer = Eitbit | publisher = Eitbit | platforms = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Windows Phone]] | released = 2012 | genre = Action | modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer]] }}
'''Soviet Challenge: Javelin 1980''' is a 2012 [[javelin throw]] [[video game]] developed by [[Eitbit]].
The game is set in the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]]. The player may make a character from one of 20 available countries, deciding on their name and appearance. The aim of the game is to win the javelin throw event, played over multiple rounds, against eleven other competitors. The game supports multiplayer and utilizes [[touch screen]] controls.<ref>https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.eitbit.sovietchallengejavelin1980</ref>
